===Pronunciation===
[,kæŋgə'ru:]
===Etymology===
From Guugu Yimidhirr (Aboriginal language) ''gangurru'' meaning ''a large grey or black kangaroo''.

===Noun===
#Member of a family of large marsupials, mainly found in Australia.
#'''Kangaroo Court''': a [[fraudulent]] or [[unjust]] trial where the decision has essentially been made in advance, usually for the purpose of providing a conviction.  Also [[show trial]].

